Taiwan Stocks: Advanced Wireless, Catcher Technology, MediaTek

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-03-02T05:53:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/chinatrust-mediatek-quanta-computer-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Taipei trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and shares are as of 1:30 p.m. close.  Taiwan’s Taiex Index fell 107.66, or 1.2 percent, to
8,619.90.    Advanced Wireless Semiconductor Co . (8086 TT) lost 1.4
percent to NT$49.20. February sales fell 26 percent to NT$88.6
million from a year earlier, the company said.  Catcher Technology Co. (2474 TT) gained 2.6 percent to
NT$136, the highest level since Jan. 3, 2008. Daiwa Securities
Capital Markets Co. raised the share-price estimate to NT$143
from NT$125, while maintaining the rating at “outperform.    MediaTek Inc . (2454 TT) surged 5 percent to NT$345.50, the
most since Dec. 3. Taiwan’s largest chip designer is considering
buying back shares following a recent decline in its stock
price, the Economic Daily News reported, citing company
executives it didn’t identify. Ching-Jiang Hsieh, spokesman for
the company, didn’t answer calls to his office.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  